The '''''Lucrehulk''-class LH-3210 cargo freighter''',<ref name="Ultimate" /> also known as a '''''Profiteer''-class freighter''',<ref name="Star Wars Journeys: The Phantom Menace">''[[Star Wars Journeys: The Phantom Menace]]''</ref> the '''''Lucrehulk''-class transport''',<ref name="Catalyst">''[[Catalyst: A Rogue One Novel]]''</ref> or the '''Lucrehulk bulk freighter''',<ref name="Rise">''[[Rise of the Separatists]]''</ref> was a [[starship]] utilized by the [[Trade Federation]] to haul freight.<ref name="Ultimate" /> By the [[time]] of the [[Clone Wars]], the ships had been used for [[Standard decade|decades]].<ref name="Catalyst" /> Many of these starships were secretly modified into [[Lucrehulk-class battleship|''Lucrehulk''-class battleships]], which saw extensive use throughout the Clone Wars.<ref name="Ultimate" /> A single Lucrehulk could have enough resources to conquer a planet.<ref name="Survivor" /> These ships were used during the [[blockade]] and [[Invasion of Naboo]],<ref name="Episode I" /> the [[First Battle of Geonosis]],<ref name="Episode II" /> and the [[Battle of Coruscant]].<ref name="Episode III">{{Film|III}}</ref> The ''Lucrehulk''-class vessel ''[[Primacy]]'' crashed into the [[planet]] [[Koboh]].<ref name="Survivor" />

